Milestone 3: Training, Evaluation, and Documentation

Main objective
Finalize the end-to-end dog breed classification system by running full training experiments, performing detailed evaluation, and preparing clear documentation/report materials for final presentation and demo.

What was implemented in this project for Milestone 3
Milestone 3 focused on completing and validating the full model lifecycle:

1) Final training execution
- File: src/train_pretrained.py
- Ran multi-epoch training with pretrained ResNet-18 and transfer learning setup.
- Tracked train and validation performance every epoch.
- Used regularization choices (label smoothing + weight decay) and class-balanced sampling in training.
- Saved both last and best checkpoints for reproducibility and model selection.

2) Final model evaluation
- File: src/evaluate.py
- Evaluated saved checkpoints on selected split (train/val/test, especially test for final result).
- Computed key metrics:
  - loss
  - top-1 accuracy
  - top-5 accuracy
- Generated detailed artifacts for analysis:
  - per-class accuracy CSV
  - full classification report (JSON)
  - confusion matrix figure

3) Inference/demo preparation
- File: src/predict.py
- Verified real inference flow on unseen single images.
- Reported top-k predicted breeds with probabilities for demo-ready output.

4) Documentation and reproducibility
- File: README.md
- Documented complete run sequence:
  - split data
  - verify pipeline
  - train
  - evaluate
  - predict
- Added local and Colab usage instructions for easier team collaboration and grading.

Structural design impact in Milestone 3
Because Milestones 1 and 2 were modular, Milestone 3 became straightforward:
- data pipeline modules handled loading/preprocessing consistently
- training script handled optimization/checkpointing/history
- evaluation script handled metrics and analysis outputs
- inference script handled demonstration use case

This modular design reduced debugging time and made final report preparation easier.

